# Agent skills in this workspace

Before **substantive** work (code changes, non-trivial refactors, multi-file edits, or detailed implementation plans) in a domain covered by a skill:

1. Open **[.agents/README.md](.agents/README.md)** and identify **which** skill folders apply to the user’s request (do not read all skills; context is limited).
2. Read **`SKILL.md`** for each selected skill (use the Read tool) and follow its instructions **where they fit** this repo’s stack (see root `AGENTS.md` and `docs/architecture.md`). Skip or adapt guidance that assumes a different framework or missing tooling.

Purely conversational questions, tiny one-line fixes with no domain skill, or doc-only typo fixes do not require loading skills unless the user asks for standards compliance.
